Reasoning: The paper deals with extensions of the lambda calculus and their properties, which are topics typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of ideal completion instead of metric completion may also be of interest to researchers in the area of topology (cs.TL). The strictness properties of the calculi may be relevant to researchers in the areas of formal languages (cs.FL) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
